Tribe 
Litini
in the subfamily 
Gelechiinae
is delimited by frequently reduced gnathos of the male genitalia; absence of culcitula; presence of glandiductors and often fused juxta with vinculum and sacculus (for more details see: Bidzilya & Mey 2011; 

). Additional characteristic features of the tribe are: strongly developed and usually modified male abdominal segment VIII; long apophyses anteriores; normally rhomboid signum with serrated edges in female genitalia (Piskunov 1973) and forewing usually with tufts of raised scales (Huemer & Karsholt 1999; 

). Tribe 
Litini
comprises about 40 genera worldwide (

; Huemer & Karsholt 1999; 

